<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="332" type="collection and habitat data">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="332">Collection and habitat data.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
This is a polyphagous species reported from hosts in 19 families (
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, SM" journalOrPublisher=", The Coleopterists Society, United States, Sacramento, CA" pageId="15" pageNumber="336" title="Host plants of leaf beetles species occurring in the United States and Canada. Coleopterists Society Special Publication No. 2." year="2004">Clark et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Most adults of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Systena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Systena hudsonias" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hudsonias">Systena hudsonias</taxonomicName>
from New Brunswick were swept from foliage in old field habitats. Adults were captured during July.
</paragraph>
